1
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:21,010
The operating system is nearly complete.
We are currently at 90%.

2
00:00:21,290 --> 00:00:22,860
As for the remaining 10%,

3
00:00:23,380 --> 00:00:27,710
we’ve programmed A382 to learn what it
means to be human by studying its owner.

4
00:00:28,330 --> 00:00:31,490
But the only thing we're missing is...

5
00:00:38,070 --> 00:00:39,070
A suitable face?

6
00:00:41,530 --> 00:00:42,380
Yes, sir.

7
00:00:53,360 --> 00:00:54,370
What do you think?

8
00:01:16,740 --> 00:01:17,900
What the hell?

9
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:19,200
Ouch!

10
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:33,160
Oh shit.

11
00:01:36,090 --> 00:01:39,039
Two more hours, P’ Ploy.
I'll send it over as soon as the render is done.

12
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:40,920
I know. You already told me.

13
00:01:42,070 --> 00:01:44,310
Huh? Then why are you calling me?

14
00:01:44,340 --> 00:01:45,560
It’s two in the morning.

15
00:01:45,590 --> 00:01:48,390
I’ve been pulling all-nighters for
three days straight now. Three days!

16
00:01:49,940 --> 00:01:50,950
There’s an urgent job.

17
00:01:51,590 --> 00:01:52,550
An urgent job?

18
00:01:56,590 --> 00:01:57,950
- No, I’m not listening.
- Listen.

19
00:01:58,110 --> 00:02:00,590
- No! I’m losing my mind right now.
- Stop and listen to me.

20
00:02:00,610 --> 00:02:02,640
The client needs it urgently by tomorrow morning.

21
00:02:02,660 --> 00:02:05,970
What?! I can’t do that.
It’s impossible. No! Way!

22
00:02:05,990 --> 00:02:07,260
Don't throw a tantrum just yet.

23
00:02:07,290 --> 00:02:08,300
- But—
- Listen!

24
00:02:10,870 --> 00:02:13,150
I know you’ve been pulling
all-nighters for three nights,

25
00:02:13,480 --> 00:02:15,700
barely showering, and
basically living on protein bars.

26
00:02:15,720 --> 00:02:18,250
But this is that regular
client who pays really well.

27
00:02:18,270 --> 00:02:20,730
The same one who lets you
cash out your advances early

28
00:02:20,750 --> 00:02:22,030
until you’ve paid off your house.

29
00:02:22,050 --> 00:02:25,210
They said they need this urgently.
Don't argue with me.

30
00:02:25,230 --> 00:02:28,000
And I know you have one finished
piece you're refusing to send.

31
00:02:30,410 --> 00:02:31,970
You know I can't send that one.

32
00:02:32,090 --> 00:02:35,040
Why not? It’s 100% your work.

33
00:02:36,150 --> 00:02:39,180
- It’s not perfect yet.
- Then it’s time to make it perfect.

34
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:40,610
Your muse.

35
00:02:41,930 --> 00:02:44,770
Before dawn. Got it?

36
00:02:57,670 --> 00:02:59,380
I used to think I had a strange job.

37
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:04,810
I tell everyone I’m a graphic designer,
but in reality…

38
00:03:10,160 --> 00:03:15,600
my job is to create... faces of people
who don't actually exist in this world.

39
00:03:19,530 --> 00:03:20,329
But

40
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:24,920
I never care what anyone does with
my illustrations, as long as I get paid...

41
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:29,070
even if it’s the face from my dreams.

42
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:38,970
Am I dreaming?

43
00:03:40,770 --> 00:03:41,770
Is it really done?

44
00:03:53,460 --> 00:03:54,329
Forget it.

45
00:03:55,070 --> 00:03:56,870
It’s sent.
It belongs to the client now.

46
00:03:57,810 --> 00:03:59,030
No use regretting it.

47
00:04:03,460 --> 00:04:04,480
Better take a shower.

48
00:04:36,750 --> 00:04:37,750
Have you seen this yet?

49
00:04:38,930 --> 00:04:40,150
Why didn't you knock?

50
00:04:45,159 --> 00:04:47,210
So you’ve seen it.
What a waste of time.

51
00:04:48,190 --> 00:04:51,630
Now we have to redesign A382's face.
This time, I want a professional.

52
00:04:52,130 --> 00:04:56,130
Even if the face resembles a real person,
it's still better than using amateurs.

53
00:04:56,700 --> 00:04:57,810
We’re using this face.

54
00:05:02,700 --> 00:05:03,700
Are you sure about this?

55
00:05:06,210 --> 00:05:07,380
But I have one condition.

56
00:05:32,460 --> 00:05:33,820
What are you so attached to, Gen?

57
00:05:34,390 --> 00:05:37,400
The person from your dreams is just
a fancy phrase that can't pay the bills.

58
00:05:49,870 --> 00:05:52,050
Yes! I’m coming! Just a moment!

59
00:05:57,630 --> 00:05:58,640
Are you Khun Jarinda?

60
00:06:00,910 --> 00:06:01,950
Are you Khun Jarinda?

61
00:06:02,850 --> 00:06:04,500
- Yes.
- Could you sign for this, please?

62
00:06:05,050 --> 00:06:06,470
Alright, haul it inside.

63
00:06:07,980 --> 00:06:10,040
- I— I didn’t order it.
- Please sign here too.

64
00:06:10,390 --> 00:06:11,280
- Here?
- Yes.

65
00:06:11,300 --> 00:06:12,570
- Hey! Hold on!
- Right here, please.

66
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:16,380
- Wait! This is trespassing!
- Have you signed yet? Right here.

67
00:06:16,450 --> 00:06:17,880
- Wait! Hold on!
- Here too.

68
00:06:17,910 --> 00:06:18,930
Oh, okay.

69
00:06:19,150 --> 00:06:20,300
Right here as well.

70
00:06:20,330 --> 00:06:21,240
Ugh!

71
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:23,450
Are you sure you didn't send this?

72
00:06:23,780 --> 00:06:25,290
It really wasn't me.

73
00:06:25,310 --> 00:06:27,410
You know I’m in Hong Kong with P’ Le.

74
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:29,510
How would I have time to
buy something and ship it?

75
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:31,030
Did you buy something yourself?

76
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:36,350
When would I have had time?
I’ve been working all month.

77
00:06:36,380 --> 00:06:40,040
Forget shopping apps, I didn't
even have time to scroll through my phone.

78
00:06:40,940 --> 00:06:44,400
Are you sure this isn’t you
and P’ Le pulling a prank on me?

79
00:06:44,850 --> 00:06:47,710
Well, the box is huge, Rann.

80
00:06:47,830 --> 00:06:49,860
It’s literally human-sized!

81
00:06:51,070 --> 00:06:53,750
If it’s not you two, then I have
no idea who would send me this.

82
00:06:55,290 --> 00:06:56,490
It really wasn’t us.

83
00:06:56,940 --> 00:06:58,659
But if you’re curious, just open it.

84
00:07:44,230 --> 00:07:45,210
What on earth...

85
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:49,130
What’s going on?

86
00:07:56,650 --> 00:07:57,500
This face...

87
00:08:32,020 --> 00:08:35,990
Greetings. I am Robot Model A382.

88
00:08:36,289 --> 00:08:38,500
My duty is to ensure user satisfaction.

89
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:44,740
Please assign me a name and state your requests.

90
00:11:07,270 --> 00:11:08,270
This makes no sense.

91
00:11:08,430 --> 00:11:10,540
Send your people to take this back immediately!

92
00:11:10,730 --> 00:11:11,880
I didn't order it.

93
00:11:11,980 --> 00:11:14,620
Some lunatic sent it to me, and it's a—

94
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:21,500
I don't care!
Send your people right now!

95
00:11:22,610 --> 00:11:24,770
What do you mean you can't?
You just have to pick it up

96
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:26,480
and return it to whoever sent it.

97
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:28,020
What?!

98
00:11:28,050 --> 00:11:29,940
The company has a no-return policy?

99
00:11:30,180 --> 00:11:31,880
This is absolutely ridiculous!

100
00:11:31,900 --> 00:11:34,300
I’m going to file a complaint
against your company!

101
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:38,080
Hello?

102
00:11:39,110 --> 00:11:39,950
Hello?!

103
00:11:40,580 --> 00:11:42,690
Hey! Did you seriously just hang up on me?

104
00:11:42,780 --> 00:11:44,330
Are you dissatisfied with me, Master?

105
00:11:45,570 --> 00:11:47,560
I told you to stay over there! Back off!

106
00:11:49,390 --> 00:11:50,970
I said don't come near me! Back off!

107
00:11:54,390 --> 00:11:55,390
Like this?

108
00:11:55,830 --> 00:11:56,630
More.

109
00:11:59,110 --> 00:11:59,890
Keep going.

110
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:02,290
All the way to the back!

111
00:12:11,190 --> 00:12:12,600
Are you satisfied now, Master?

112
00:12:12,980 --> 00:12:13,680
No.

113
00:12:17,660 --> 00:12:19,010
Are you angry with me, Master?

114
00:12:19,540 --> 00:12:20,450
Because you—

115
00:12:20,850 --> 00:12:22,530
Did I do something wrong?

116
00:12:33,750 --> 00:12:34,640
Whatever.

117
00:12:35,340 --> 00:12:37,160
Don’t you ever leave that spot.

118
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:39,880
Understood, Master.

119
00:12:42,270 --> 00:12:43,270
Good.

120
00:12:44,770 --> 00:12:45,890
But I’m not your "Master."

121
00:12:51,640 --> 00:12:54,610
Are you... really a robot?

122
00:12:56,350 --> 00:12:58,100
Would you like me to prove it, Master?

123
00:13:18,270 --> 00:13:20,280
Hey! What the hell are you doing?!

124
00:13:20,540 --> 00:13:21,710
Are you insane?!

125
00:13:21,860 --> 00:13:23,970
- I’m proving it.
- Proving what?!

126
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:26,010
You’re trying to commit suicide in my house—

127
00:13:31,630 --> 00:13:32,420
Huh?

128
00:13:48,970 --> 00:13:49,980
Do you believe me now?

129
00:13:56,660 --> 00:13:59,730
Shit, what do I do?
Call the delivery company.

130
00:14:00,470 --> 00:14:01,500
Or a mental asylum?

131
00:14:01,870 --> 00:14:04,100
- Would you like me to help you?
- No, no, no, no! No!

132
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:06,540
Stay out of it. Don’t help.
Don’t do anything at all!

133
00:14:08,070 --> 00:14:08,940
I’m going crazy!

134
00:14:10,860 --> 00:14:14,700
According to company policy, we truly
cannot accept returns for this item, ma'am.

135
00:14:15,060 --> 00:14:17,110
You're the tenth person to tell me that.

136
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:19,380
We truly apologize for this.

137
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,350
If you feel sorry,
then come and take it back!

138
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:22,940
We are truly sorry.

139
00:14:34,340 --> 00:14:36,260
Are you ready to assign me a name, Master?

140
00:14:39,430 --> 00:14:40,580
Where exactly are you from?

141
00:14:41,540 --> 00:14:43,190
That information is company confidential.

142
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:45,610
Then why did the company send you?

143
00:14:45,640 --> 00:14:47,190
That information is company confidential.

144
00:14:47,220 --> 00:14:49,590
- Why my house?
- That information is company confidential.

145
00:14:49,610 --> 00:14:50,790
Then why me?!

146
00:14:52,640 --> 00:14:54,370
That information is company confidential.

147
00:14:54,610 --> 00:14:55,300
Hey!

148
00:14:56,260 --> 00:14:59,060
If it’s so confidential,
then why are you even here?

149
00:14:59,090 --> 00:15:00,350
Go back to your company!

150
00:15:00,830 --> 00:15:03,740
I can't send you back,
but you have legs, don't you?

151
00:15:03,940 --> 00:15:06,070
Since you won't tell me
anything, go back on your own!

152
00:15:06,650 --> 00:15:09,360
You should know where
that stupid factory is, right?

153
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:12,460
I cannot do that.

154
00:15:13,590 --> 00:15:15,130
You can't do this, you can't do that!

155
00:15:16,250 --> 00:15:18,140
I have to satisfy you first.

156
00:15:18,990 --> 00:15:20,130
What are you talking about?!

157
00:15:20,430 --> 00:15:23,540
I am a robot designed to
ensure user satisfaction.

158
00:15:23,570 --> 00:15:26,250
If Master is not satisfied,
I cannot return.

159
00:15:30,710 --> 00:15:33,680
- Please assign a name.
- Satisfied! I’m satisfied!

160
00:15:49,820 --> 00:15:51,870
Based on the scan,

161
00:15:52,180 --> 00:15:55,550
your pupils are dilated and
your heart rate has elevated.

162
00:15:55,580 --> 00:16:00,320
This indicates a reaction as you prepare
to handle what it perceives as a threat.

163
00:16:02,220 --> 00:16:06,930
In conclusion, you are not exhibiting
metrics of happiness or satisfaction.

164
00:16:07,350 --> 00:16:09,940
Rather, your body is
responding to natural mechanisms

165
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:11,800
controlled by the autonomic nervous system

166
00:16:11,820 --> 00:16:12,820
- ...and hormo—
- Stop!

167
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:15,870
Stop it.

168
00:16:16,150 --> 00:16:19,600
Who gave you permission to read
my pupils or my heartbeat? Stop it!

169
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:24,540
I have stopped.

170
00:16:28,680 --> 00:16:31,180
- Please assign a name.
- Ugh! I'm not naming you!

171
00:16:31,210 --> 00:16:32,210
I’m not doing anything!

172
00:16:33,230 --> 00:16:35,450
Do you want me to stand here all night, Master?

173
00:16:49,050 --> 00:16:52,570
I'm… not that cruel.

174
00:17:00,190 --> 00:17:01,640
Why are you looking at me like that?

175
00:17:04,650 --> 00:17:05,650
Is it not working?

176
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:06,810
What?

177
00:17:07,690 --> 00:17:11,150
Statistically, humans tend to prefer cute beings.

178
00:17:13,060 --> 00:17:15,680
So I act… cute.

179
00:17:16,540 --> 00:17:17,990
Your heart should soften, Master.

180
00:17:19,510 --> 00:17:21,079
Gosh, don't read my mind! Stop it!

181
00:17:21,589 --> 00:17:26,760
I don’t care if you sit, sleep, or whatever—
just don’t step into my bedroom.

182
00:17:26,780 --> 00:17:29,590
And remember,
I’m not letting you stay here.

183
00:17:29,910 --> 00:17:31,570
I’m going to find a way to send you back.

184
00:17:32,990 --> 00:17:34,550
- Master?
- What now?!

185
00:17:35,570 --> 00:17:36,840
Good night.

186
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:07,440
Yes.

187
00:18:08,830 --> 00:18:09,610
Of course.

188
00:18:10,460 --> 00:18:11,690
No problem at all.

189
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:14,810
Sis, I sent it over.

190
00:18:15,740 --> 00:18:17,910
One sec. I’m on a call.

191
00:18:18,580 --> 00:18:21,080
Yes, absolutely.

192
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:24,740
I guarantee you the designer
will keep completely quiet about it.

193
00:18:24,900 --> 00:18:27,610
Trust me, we’ve worked together many times.

194
00:18:27,630 --> 00:18:31,040
I assure you this fabric pattern
will be exclusively yours, Khun Nin.

195
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:32,150
Okay.

196
00:18:34,260 --> 00:18:35,100
P’ Ploy.

197
00:18:37,660 --> 00:18:38,670
What’s gotten into you?

198
00:18:40,290 --> 00:18:43,830
I want a list of clients who bought my work.
Who did you sell it to?

199
00:18:44,110 --> 00:18:45,570
We already agreed that—

200
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:48,250
Work goes out, money comes in.
No questions about the client's identity.

201
00:18:48,280 --> 00:18:49,800
I know. I know it perfectly well.

202
00:18:50,390 --> 00:18:52,730
Did you forget how many years
I’ve been working for you?

203
00:18:53,330 --> 00:18:55,670
Well. If you know that,
then why are you asking?

204
00:18:55,780 --> 00:18:57,410
I need to return something to them.

205
00:18:57,720 --> 00:18:58,600
What is it?

206
00:18:58,930 --> 00:18:59,700
It’s—

207
00:19:03,850 --> 00:19:06,870
I just do, okay?
Why are you even asking?

208
00:19:07,670 --> 00:19:11,880
Hey, beautiful.
What got you so worked up?

209
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:13,790
Come on, tell me about it.

210
00:19:14,670 --> 00:19:15,670
Get your hand off me.

211
00:19:15,880 --> 00:19:17,260
No can do.

212
00:19:19,300 --> 00:19:21,790
So are you going to tell me or not, P’ Ploy?

213
00:19:21,850 --> 00:19:24,130
No. We already talked about this.

214
00:19:24,930 --> 00:19:27,830
You know I take on all kinds of art commissions.

215
00:19:27,850 --> 00:19:32,190
The money is great, but the sole condition
is that we remain completely anonymous.

216
00:19:32,210 --> 00:19:34,550
The client purchases
the work with full copyright.

217
00:19:34,740 --> 00:19:38,840
Every face you’ve been paid for
is no longer yours to take back.

218
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:43,360
Even if I’m just a commission agent,
I have my own ethics to uphold.

219
00:19:44,010 --> 00:19:44,790
Got it?

220
00:19:46,970 --> 00:19:50,800
So who exactly made
my pretty little sis this furious?

221
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:08,880
Good morning, Master.

222
00:20:10,680 --> 00:20:12,550
Please assign me a name.

223
00:20:22,300 --> 00:20:24,860
P’ Petch, could I have
the return address, please?

224
00:20:26,650 --> 00:20:30,280
If I give it to you, she’ll kill me.

225
00:20:32,970 --> 00:20:36,950
P’ Ploy, please help me.
I’m in real trouble here.

226
00:20:37,090 --> 00:20:38,190
I can’t give it to you.

227
00:20:38,270 --> 00:20:39,560
P’ Ploy!

228
00:20:40,850 --> 00:20:41,660
No.

229
00:20:42,850 --> 00:20:44,670
P’ Ploy...

230
00:20:44,860 --> 00:20:47,750
Alright, fine. How about this?

231
00:20:47,770 --> 00:20:52,270
If the client contacts us,
I’ll ask if they’ll accept the return.

232
00:20:53,410 --> 00:20:56,120
Don’t smile. Don’t wai.
I haven’t agreed yet.

233
00:20:57,950 --> 00:21:00,780
Then contact them right now, P' Ploy.

234
00:21:01,170 --> 00:21:03,380
Our policy is not to contact clients.

235
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:07,330
If they don’t reach out first,
there’s nothing I can do.

236
00:21:14,290 --> 00:21:15,130
Here.

237
00:21:16,100 --> 00:21:18,670
Something sweet for the stress.

238
00:22:08,560 --> 00:22:09,430
How unusual.

239
00:22:14,120 --> 00:22:16,360
Requesting purchase authorization.

240
00:22:40,110 --> 00:22:43,140
Here’s Auntie Kai's mouthwatering,
tongue-tingling chicken pad kaphrao!

241
00:22:43,540 --> 00:22:46,670
Wow! The way you described it
kinda killed my appetite.

242
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:48,510
Too bad.
You're paying for it anyway.

243
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:52,420
I haven't even taken a bite.
Why do I have to pay?

244
00:22:52,440 --> 00:22:53,520
'Cause I already made it.

245
00:22:53,540 --> 00:22:56,710
Whether you eat it or not is your problem.
I made it, so you pay for it.

246
00:22:56,740 --> 00:22:58,050
Come on, Auntie!

247
00:22:58,580 --> 00:23:00,070
If you eat it, you gotta pay.

248
00:23:02,270 --> 00:23:03,980
Khun Gen! You're here!

249
00:23:05,110 --> 00:23:06,760
Wait, wait, wait!
What's the rush?

250
00:23:07,040 --> 00:23:09,390
- What is it, Auntie?
- Where are you going? Hold on!

251
00:23:09,750 --> 00:23:11,540
Why are you trying to run away?

252
00:23:11,840 --> 00:23:13,260
Just look at your face.

253
00:23:14,420 --> 00:23:16,430
No answers, no comments.
I don’t know anything.

254
00:23:17,460 --> 00:23:18,470
I haven't asked yet!

255
00:23:18,810 --> 00:23:20,120
But you're going to, aren't you?

256
00:23:20,470 --> 00:23:22,360
You know how many years I’ve lived around here.

257
00:23:22,650 --> 00:23:25,720
How could I not know where
all the nonsense rumors start?

258
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:30,740
So, no answers, no comments.
I don't know anything.

259
00:23:31,840 --> 00:23:32,840
I’ve gone bonkers.

260
00:23:34,190 --> 00:23:35,490
Just one question.

261
00:23:37,890 --> 00:23:38,580
No.

262
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:40,740
What did you order the other day?

263
00:23:42,270 --> 00:23:44,970
Word is it was a human-sized box.

264
00:23:45,850 --> 00:23:49,940
I didn't start this, but people are
saying you ordered a coffin to your house!

265
00:23:50,660 --> 00:23:52,260
Gen, that’s bad luck!

266
00:23:52,290 --> 00:23:54,890
If you really ordered it,
get it out of the house immediately!

267
00:23:55,130 --> 00:23:56,740
But why would you order a coffin anyway?

268
00:23:57,900 --> 00:23:59,030
You live alone.

269
00:23:59,740 --> 00:24:00,990
Or am I out of the loop?

270
00:24:01,340 --> 00:24:03,390
- Or did you accidentally kill someone?
- Auntie!

271
00:24:04,120 --> 00:24:05,280
What is it? Tell me!

272
00:24:05,460 --> 00:24:08,160
If you’re not going to sell me food,
I’ll buy from another shop.

273
00:24:08,190 --> 00:24:11,310
Gen. Of course I'm selling!

274
00:24:12,980 --> 00:24:14,800
Why would you go anywhere else?

275
00:24:14,830 --> 00:24:18,380
I make the absolute best pad kaphrao
in this entire neighborhood.

276
00:24:19,250 --> 00:24:21,820
Gen! Don’t be like this!

277
00:24:21,840 --> 00:24:24,310
Why so impatient?
Don’t act like a hot-headed teenager!

278
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:26,500
How about chicken pad
kaphrao with a fried egg?

279
00:24:26,880 --> 00:24:27,700
Make it two.

280
00:24:29,270 --> 00:24:31,080
- Are you on your period?
- Auntie.

281
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:34,980
If you ask me one more question,
I’m walking straight out to another shop.

282
00:24:35,580 --> 00:24:38,990
And if a rumor goes around that Gen is
on her period and eating like a monster,

283
00:24:39,010 --> 00:24:40,670
I’ll never come to your place ever again.

284
00:24:45,410 --> 00:24:46,890
Pay when you’re done eating!

285
00:24:52,160 --> 00:24:53,510
- Honey.
- Yes, babe?

286
00:24:53,530 --> 00:24:55,270
We have to finish the series today.

287
00:24:55,370 --> 00:24:58,300
- Oh, last episode was such a cliffhanger.
- Last night—

288
00:24:58,460 --> 00:25:01,010
Wait, are you starting to go gray?

289
00:25:01,030 --> 00:25:02,620
- What?! Really?!
- Yeah.

290
00:25:02,640 --> 00:25:03,960
- Look.
- Eek! I’m getting old!

291
00:25:03,980 --> 00:25:05,940
- But it’s okay, you’re still adorable.
- Really?

292
00:25:05,970 --> 00:25:07,760
Really? Really? Do I have a lot?

293
00:25:07,790 --> 00:25:10,980
Wow, look at Mr. and
Mrs. Madly-in-Love over here.

294
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:13,430
Getting all lovey-dovey
first thing in the morning.

295
00:25:13,530 --> 00:25:16,450
Morning, my ass.
It's almost evening already, Ai Josh.

296
00:25:16,470 --> 00:25:18,580
I told you to stop gaming overnight.

297
00:25:18,770 --> 00:25:21,740
You don't feel it now, but
you’ll regret it when you're older.

298
00:25:21,770 --> 00:25:24,550
P’ Zoon, tell your wife I’m not your kid.

299
00:25:24,580 --> 00:25:27,020
What time I sleep is my business.

300
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:31,100
She’s only warning you because she cares.
Just listen to her, Josh.

301
00:25:31,710 --> 00:25:33,330
- Right, P’ Zoon?
- Of course, baby.

302
00:25:33,350 --> 00:25:34,730
Hey, P’ Gen’s back.

303
00:25:36,210 --> 00:25:38,450
Escaped the boss only to
run straight into her henchmen.

304
00:25:40,020 --> 00:25:43,660
Nong Gen! Where have you been?

305
00:25:44,660 --> 00:25:48,020
Did you order a lot of stuff?
I saw the delivery guys coming nonstop.

306
00:25:49,080 --> 00:25:50,140
Ow!

307
00:25:50,170 --> 00:25:51,390
What’s wrong? Where does it hurt?

308
00:25:51,410 --> 00:25:53,160
- P' Zoon, call an ambulance!
- It hurts so bad.

309
00:25:53,180 --> 00:25:56,040
- What do we do? Is it your appendix?
- Where's my phone? Call the doctor!

310
00:25:56,070 --> 00:25:57,330
- What’s wrong, Nong Gen?
- Ugh!

311
00:25:59,150 --> 00:26:01,570
I need to poop. Right now.

312
00:26:02,130 --> 00:26:03,990
- It’s coming!
- Hey! Gen!

313
00:26:04,020 --> 00:26:05,150
Gotta go. Gotta go. Gotta go!

314
00:26:05,300 --> 00:26:07,880
Hey! She’s gone. So fast.

315
00:26:15,030 --> 00:26:16,260
Should I just move?

316
00:26:20,820 --> 00:26:22,550
Can robots even eat?

317
00:26:27,660 --> 00:26:30,760
Whatever, I already bought it.
Come what may.

318
00:26:35,530 --> 00:26:36,640
Master.

319
00:26:36,660 --> 00:26:37,720
I bought some food—

320
00:26:45,430 --> 00:26:46,990
Are you satisfied, Master?

321
00:27:02,860 --> 00:27:04,110
I’m definitely daydreaming.

322
00:27:04,130 --> 00:27:06,200
Auntie Kai must’ve put
something weird in the food. No.

323
00:27:06,220 --> 00:27:08,400
Gen, you’re just sleep-deprived.
Go to bed.

324
00:27:08,650 --> 00:27:10,160
Yes, yes, go to bed now.

325
00:27:18,680 --> 00:27:20,900
That face... that outfit...

326
00:27:21,650 --> 00:27:22,530
This is insane.

327
00:27:41,130 --> 00:27:42,320
Don't look at me like that.

328
00:27:42,850 --> 00:27:45,970
I’m not having any dirty thoughts.
I don't want to see at all.

329
00:27:47,270 --> 00:27:49,260
Who would have such thoughts
about their own muse?

330
00:27:58,010 --> 00:27:59,270
Ugh, I’m going crazy!

331
00:28:03,540 --> 00:28:06,200
I need to sleep.
Yes, I need to sleep.

332
00:28:06,690 --> 00:28:07,870
Go to sleep, Gen.

333
00:28:11,730 --> 00:28:13,210
Are you ready, Captain?

334
00:28:19,450 --> 00:28:20,550
Thanks...

335
00:28:20,570 --> 00:28:21,730
Coffee or me?

336
00:28:33,170 --> 00:28:35,600
Do you prefer rabbits or cats, Master?

337
00:28:35,860 --> 00:28:37,330
Meow.

338
00:28:39,050 --> 00:28:41,630
THAT IS ENOUGH!!!!

339
00:28:47,020 --> 00:28:49,300
I'm very satisfied! Extremely satisfied!

340
00:28:49,320 --> 00:28:51,550
I’ve never been this satisfied in my entire life!

341
00:28:53,990 --> 00:28:55,050
You are lying, Master.

342
00:28:55,540 --> 00:28:58,200
I’m not lying. Don’t accuse me.

343
00:28:58,430 --> 00:29:00,970
And where on earth did you
get these ridiculous outfits from?!

344
00:29:03,890 --> 00:29:05,410
I ordered them online.

345
00:29:05,430 --> 00:29:07,730
Would you like me to specify
the application, Master?

346
00:29:07,750 --> 00:29:11,110
But from the content I have studied,
company names are often avoided.

347
00:29:11,140 --> 00:29:14,290
Would you like me to state the name
directly or indirectly, Master?

348
00:29:14,310 --> 00:29:16,970
Whether I name it directly,
indirectly, or abbreviate it,

349
00:29:16,990 --> 00:29:20,460
if people can identify the company,
it can still lead to legal action.

350
00:29:24,350 --> 00:29:25,940
What am I supposed to do with you?

351
00:29:26,350 --> 00:29:29,610
I don't know the address to return you,
and kicking you out makes me feel guilty.

352
00:29:30,470 --> 00:29:32,320
Look. At least, you robot girl—

353
00:29:32,780 --> 00:29:33,780
Are you addressing me?

354
00:29:34,290 --> 00:29:36,940
Who else, me?! I’m talking to you!

355
00:29:37,300 --> 00:29:38,770
Can you just stay put for once?

356
00:29:50,680 --> 00:29:51,500
What are you doing?

357
00:29:53,930 --> 00:29:56,590
Making cute expression.
It usually softens human hearts.

358
00:29:57,090 --> 00:29:58,440
Has your heart softened yet, Master?

359
00:30:00,250 --> 00:30:01,000
You—!

360
00:30:04,340 --> 00:30:06,210
Ugh! Whatever.

361
00:30:07,340 --> 00:30:10,900
Until I find a way to send you back, stay put.

362
00:30:11,520 --> 00:30:12,580
I’m asking you nicely.

363
00:30:14,290 --> 00:30:15,150
A name.

364
00:30:17,190 --> 00:30:18,410
I want a name.

365
00:30:20,130 --> 00:30:22,310
Well… Robot Girl.

366
00:30:28,140 --> 00:30:29,000
What are you doing?

367
00:30:30,830 --> 00:30:32,220
Acting cute.

368
00:30:35,450 --> 00:30:37,380
Hey, stop! What are you doing?!

369
00:30:38,720 --> 00:30:40,650
Exposing my belly for you to rub, Master.

370
00:30:41,430 --> 00:30:43,470
Meow.

371
00:30:43,780 --> 00:30:46,370
What?
What kind of madness is this?!

372
00:30:46,720 --> 00:30:48,670
Meow...

373
00:30:51,070 --> 00:30:54,400
Alright, alright, alright! I get it!
I get it! Your name is—!

374
00:30:56,950 --> 00:30:57,720
Ai.

375
00:31:00,950 --> 00:31:02,590
Please confirm the name.

376
00:31:04,780 --> 00:31:06,640
Your name is Ai.

377
00:31:08,010 --> 00:31:08,680
Like…

378
00:31:11,200 --> 00:31:13,310
AI. Yeah.

379
00:31:14,240 --> 00:31:15,230
Satisfied now?

380
00:31:17,960 --> 00:31:20,250
Thank you, Khun Gen.

381
00:31:29,040 --> 00:31:31,600
Even though you did not put any thought into it.

382
00:31:36,380 --> 00:31:37,450
Glad you're satisfied.

383
00:31:39,360 --> 00:31:40,640
I’m going to work.

384
00:31:43,530 --> 00:31:44,790
Yes, Khun Gen.

385
00:32:05,480 --> 00:32:06,890
She feels warm just like a human.

386
00:32:10,950 --> 00:32:13,140
Ai Gen, what are you thinking?

387
00:32:17,630 --> 00:32:18,600
Alright.

388
00:32:21,290 --> 00:32:24,610
Just you wait. I’ll use every
hacking trick I’ve got up my sleeve.

389
00:32:24,640 --> 00:32:26,200
I’m going to send you back.

390
00:32:26,220 --> 00:32:29,140
What robot is this much of a handful?
Who could possibly put up…

391
00:32:31,300 --> 00:32:33,400
Meow…

392
00:32:34,550 --> 00:32:35,770
...with her?

393
00:32:41,340 --> 00:32:42,170
Let’s do it.

394
00:32:55,040 --> 00:32:57,920
Minister! You can't just enter
the research area like this!

395
00:32:58,120 --> 00:32:59,220
Why can't I?

396
00:32:59,350 --> 00:33:02,040
Every penny of this research
funding comes from me. Out of my way.

397
00:33:02,520 --> 00:33:04,820
I need to speak with the person
in charge of this project.

398
00:33:11,560 --> 00:33:14,050
That would be me, Minister.

399
00:33:14,610 --> 00:33:17,010
Good. We need to talk.

400
00:33:18,090 --> 00:33:20,290
What brings you all the way here, sir?

401
00:33:20,500 --> 00:33:21,750
Don’t play dumb with me.

402
00:33:22,770 --> 00:33:24,690
It’s about the robot replica of my daughter.

403
00:33:24,730 --> 00:33:26,880
When is this ridiculous
testing going to be finished?

404
00:33:28,500 --> 00:33:31,240
I can’t wait any longer.
My wife is on the verge of losing her mind!

405
00:33:36,330 --> 00:33:37,900
We’re in the final stage of testing.

406
00:33:38,810 --> 00:33:39,960
What testing?

407
00:33:41,240 --> 00:33:42,500
Real-life testing, sir.

408
00:33:46,200 --> 00:33:48,480
Surely you don’t want just any robot.

409
00:33:49,720 --> 00:33:52,290
You want a replacement
for your daughter, don’t you?

410
00:33:53,790 --> 00:33:57,060
Or do you really think your wife
would accept her like that?

411
00:33:58,680 --> 00:34:02,900
I’ve already wasted billions
on this stupid project.

412
00:34:08,239 --> 00:34:10,030
But if you get your daughter back…

413
00:34:11,980 --> 00:34:13,000
isn't it worth it?

414
00:34:17,870 --> 00:34:21,090
Two months.
I’m giving you two more months.

415
00:34:22,800 --> 00:34:24,179
- But—
- That’s all you get.

416
00:34:24,239 --> 00:34:27,090
If you still can’t succeed, you’re screwed.

417
00:34:39,590 --> 00:34:42,250
How is this even possible?
This makes no sense.

418
00:34:43,449 --> 00:34:44,980
How could I find nothing at all?

419
00:34:45,010 --> 00:34:47,870
The address, the sender's name—it's all fake!

420
00:34:48,389 --> 00:34:50,489
And there’s no shipping record either.

421
00:34:51,870 --> 00:34:52,960
What the hell is going on?!

422
00:34:57,600 --> 00:34:58,290
Ah!

423
00:35:03,950 --> 00:35:05,290
That was close.

424
00:35:50,170 --> 00:35:52,400
I don’t know how I’m supposed
to send her back anymore.

425
00:36:11,090 --> 00:36:12,280
What are you up to again?

426
00:36:13,410 --> 00:36:14,530
I'm examining this.

427
00:36:22,510 --> 00:36:24,340
I'm currently analyzing this bracelet.

428
00:36:24,620 --> 00:36:26,940
I’ve noticed you wear this bracelet all the time,

429
00:36:27,060 --> 00:36:30,640
and the beads show signs
of wear from frequent rubbing.

430
00:36:30,900 --> 00:36:35,080
Does this behavior indicate that you
have a strong attachment to this object?

431
00:36:35,440 --> 00:36:38,500
That’s why I’m analyzing what to do about...

432
00:36:38,520 --> 00:36:39,500
- the torn condition—
- Give it back!

433
00:37:00,220 --> 00:37:02,320
The woven thread has
reached the end of its lifespan.

434
00:37:02,540 --> 00:37:05,170
I can order an exact replacement for you.

435
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:09,580
As for identical beads,
I’ll need some time to search.

436
00:37:09,720 --> 00:37:13,620
I can find ones with about
95.6% similarity to the original.

437
00:37:14,350 --> 00:37:15,360
What would you know?

438
00:37:16,320 --> 00:37:19,020
My important item isn’t
a learning tool for a robot like you.

439
00:37:20,850 --> 00:37:22,400
Don't you ever touch my things again.

440
00:37:26,760 --> 00:37:30,050
And if I do, what will you do?

441
00:37:35,450 --> 00:37:36,770
I don’t want to talk to you.

442
00:38:02,640 --> 00:38:05,190
It’s broken, so just let it go, Gen.

443
00:38:06,150 --> 00:38:07,800
How many years has it been?

444
00:38:09,060 --> 00:38:10,240
But still...

445
00:38:26,920 --> 00:38:29,330
How could you take it out on
something that isn’t even human?

446
00:38:36,680 --> 00:38:39,840
Even if she’s a robot, you
had no right to say those things.

447
00:38:40,430 --> 00:38:41,750
"Emotionless"?

448
00:38:42,400 --> 00:38:45,480
How could you say that?
You're not that kind of person.

449
00:38:47,640 --> 00:38:50,950
I am a robot designed to
ensure user satisfaction.

450
00:38:52,160 --> 00:38:54,480
Do you want me to stand here all night, Master?

451
00:38:59,440 --> 00:39:01,800
Thank you, Khun Gen.

452
00:39:03,650 --> 00:39:06,110
Ugh! I'm going crazy!

453
00:39:06,680 --> 00:39:08,000
The guilt is eating me alive!

454
00:39:10,870 --> 00:39:12,090
Fine! I’m sorry!

455
00:39:12,690 --> 00:39:15,530
Conscience, ethics, morality—
stop shouting in my head.

456
00:39:17,790 --> 00:39:19,010
I'll just go apologize.

457
00:39:31,990 --> 00:39:32,670
Ai.

458
00:39:40,630 --> 00:39:41,380
Ai.

459
00:39:42,970 --> 00:39:43,800
AI.

460
00:39:50,910 --> 00:39:52,250
Come out, robot.

461
00:40:00,530 --> 00:40:01,310
Ai.

462
00:40:21,540 --> 00:40:22,870
Oh shit!

463
00:40:35,480 --> 00:40:38,730
And if I do, what will you do?

464
00:40:40,840 --> 00:40:42,110
I don’t want to talk to you.

465
00:40:55,560 --> 00:40:59,720
What do you think A382 is
going to learn from this person?

466
00:41:04,070 --> 00:41:05,150
I don't know either.

467
00:41:06,640 --> 00:41:08,090
We’ll just have to wait and see.

468
00:41:42,130 --> 00:41:44,000
Do you know that you’re mean, Gen?

469
00:41:44,900 --> 00:41:48,210
You're saying I’m mean?
Do you even know what ‘mean’ means?

470
00:41:49,020 --> 00:41:55,100
I don’t understand what anger, pain,
despair, or loving someone feel like.

471
00:41:55,610 --> 00:41:56,710
I'll help you.

472
00:41:57,130 --> 00:41:58,510
Hey! Ai!

473
00:42:00,800 --> 00:42:02,230
Can you teach me, Gen?

474
00:42:04,130 --> 00:42:06,960
I promise I won't chase you away anymore.

475
00:42:07,410 --> 00:42:08,820
And I won't shut you down either.

476
00:42:10,910 --> 00:42:12,050
Oh! sorry!

477
00:42:12,770 --> 00:42:13,520
Kaew.

